supplementary-signs.title: Distance
supplementary-signs.desc: Advance warning about where the main sign goes into effect, or where a corresponding sign is set up.

supplementary-signs.title: Stretch
supplementary-signs.desc: Main sign is in effect for the given distance.

supplementary-signs.title: Time
supplementary-signs.desc: Main sign is only in effect between given times. Black numbers in parenthesis apply on Saturdays, and red numbers apply on Sundays and official holidays.

supplementary-signs.title: Car
supplementary-signs.desc: Main sign applies to this type of vehicle.

supplementary-signs.title: Goods van, lorry and tractor unit
Handicapped driver
supplementary-signs.desc: Requires a visible parking permit for handicapped drivers.

supplementary-signs.title: Text
supplementary-signs.desc: Used when there are no symbols that represent the regulation or information. Depicted sign is common and says: “Does not apply to buses and taxis”.

supplementary-signs.title: Turn arrow
supplementary-signs.desc: Arrows vary. Main sign applies after the turn.

supplementary-signs.title: Course of priority road
supplementary-signs.desc: Symbol varies. Priority road is represented by the thick line. Roads represented by thin lines have give way or stop signs for the priority road.

supplementary-signs.title: Direction for a stop or parking regulation sign
Direction for a stop or parking regulation sign
Direction for a stop or parking regulation sign
Parking board
supplementary-signs.desc: Indicates that parking is only allowed by given regulations when a valid parking ticket or disc is placed highly visible inside the windshield.

supplementary-signs.title: Combined regulation
supplementary-signs.desc: In this example, the times written only applies for cars.
